Distribution channels play a crucial role in the accessibility and availability of green tea products to consumers. Supermarkets/hypermarkets, as major distribution channels, offer a wide array of green tea brands, providing consumers with diverse options and convenience. Specialty stores cater to specific segments of the market, appealing to consumers seeking premium or organic green tea products. The online retail segment has witnessed significant growth, driven by the increasing trend of e-commerce and consumer preference for convenient shopping experiences.

